de darstellt.  afunded by Swiss National Science Foundation (SNSF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCreative ability. 0aCultural industries. 0aFashion. 0aSociology. 4aCreative Industries. 4aGesellschaft. 4aInnovationsforschung. 4aMode. 4aNeo-Institutionalismus. 4aOrganisationsforschung. 4aOrganisationssoziologie. 4aSoziologie. 4aSprache. 4aTechnik. 4aTechniksoziologie. 4aTechnologie. 4aVariation. 4aWandel. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aChange.  aCreative Industries.  aFashion Studies.  aInnovation.  aLanguage.  aNeo-institutionalism.  aOrganization Studies.  aSociology of Organizations.  aTechnology.  aVariation.2 aSwiss National Science Foundation (SNSF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839449929zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839449929/original  a978-3-11-071956-7 DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DSWb2019  aZDB-23-GOA